The paper deals with the design of binary polarization kernels, which are used in error-correction coding. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses code decompositions, which is a technique commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves constructing non-linear kernels, which could be considered a topic in data structures (cs.DS) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the asymptotic error-correction performance of the constructed kernels, which could be seen as a topic in data mining (cs.DM).
